						<summary>

						<p>On the celling of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Kōdaṇḍarāmasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1694, Nandana, Māgha, śu. 10.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift for providing offerings and burning a perpetual lamp in the temple by Rāmaya-śeṭṭi, Rāchaya-śeṭṭi and Varadaya-śeṭṭi, sons of Papi-śeṭṭi and grandson of Māchaya-śeṭṭi of Midhuna-kula-gōtra.</p>						

						</summary>
